<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-283-069  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 283 069.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Jan 24 1989 v3 n4 p9(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Apple refines host interface developer kit. (MacWorkStation 3.1)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Farber, Daniel.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   MacWorkStation 3.1 (Program development software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionProgram Development ToolsEnhancements.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Apple refines host interface developer kitandM;SAN FRANCISCO -- A new version of MacWorkStation, announced at the MacworldExpo last week, gives improved color support, error-handling and robustnessto Apple's Mac-to-mainframe toolkit.andM;The development system allows mainframe programmers to give host applicationsaccessed from the Macintosh the look and feel of local Mac applications,without requiring host programmers to learn Macintosh programming.andP;  It alsoreduces the burden on host CPU resources and line traffic.andM;The main focus of the new Version 3.1 is to cut down program development timeand offer more aspects of the Macintosh user interface, according to productmanager Norman Kline.andP;  Among the new features in Version 3.1 are:andM;* Full-color QuickDraw support for components of the user interface, such asdialog boxes and windows.andM;* Improvements in the Presentation Layer, including error reporting to remoteapplications or local users.andM;* Director Toolbox enhancements that provide list sorting, pop-up andhierarchical menus, event locking and unlocking, field-level editing, andmultiple fonts and styles.andM;* Dialog Builder, an object-oriented tool for creating dialog boxes withoutwriting lines of code.andM;* Event Handler and Event Player, which allow applications to be debuggedwithout a host connection.andM;* Communications modules for 3270 emulation, which will be available throughApple Programmer's andamp; Developer's Association.andM;Licensees of MacWorkStation 3.0 will receive a free upgrade to the newversion.andP;  Multi-user licenses for MacWorkStation are available through AppleSoftware Licensing.andO;</TEXT></DOC>